          <div class="date" style="text-align:right;float:right;">8.4.2004</div><br /><br />
     
     
     <font class="TallRed">cars, falls, and consumerism (oh and self-improvement masturbation)<a name="109161352617789593">&nbsp;</a></font>
		<div class="blackjustified" style="background-color:#eeeeee;padding:5px 5px 5px 5px;border-top:3px solid #cccccc;border-bottom:1px solid #333333;border-left:1px solid #cccccc;border-right:1px solid #cccccc;">
          Of cars... well I've made it a point to figure out the enjoyment that people derive from archetypal hobbies and interests of masculine origin. A few weeks ago I discovered the joy of fishing, and most recently I discovered that of cars. Of course, recently acquiring a nice shiny toy of a caracas red 3000gt will stimulate these kinds of things, but I thought I'd let it be known. I couldn't sleep last night so I grabbed my keys and sat in my car in the parking lot of the barracks, wishing I could just be flying down the road with no destination nor origin to drive back to. (and not have to worry about gas--when will they invent everlasting fusion cells??!) True, there's a certain sense of peace that bringin it back to our natural roots (ie fishing) lends, but there's also another sense of peace within the cockpit of a man-made monster. It's as if for a few moments of my day I'm allowed to be one with my car--Spinning limbs of rubber grabbing and clawing towards the next moment; rumbling breaths and a fixed, angry demeanor staring down whatever is in my way: Outlets for the facets of my personality that have no place in my personal nor professional life...<br /><br />Of falls...no, not like, water falls, more like, falling off an aircraft and hairline fracturing my shin bones. Whatever those are called. But they hurt. Not enough to be broken, just hairline fractured. It's like a deep throbbing pain from inside my bones that I know is NOT supposed to be there. Hope it heals. I'm a survivor. I know it'll heal.<br /><br />And lastly, of consumerism... I used to pride myself on the fact that money was always the last thing on my mind. I'd always tip waaaay more than I ought to, with no reason other than the waitress might have had a nice smile. (I usually forget by the time it's tip-leavin' time) Whenever I'd be rung up and notice a change box sitting on the counter--even if the sale came out to $4.01--every last bit of change would end up in there. I wouldn't even take the damn mint. And I don't think I've ever been to a movie w/ a girl w/o paying for her, FRIEND OR MORE YOU'RE NOT PAYING DAMMIT. But lately, it's all been about the car. Granted, I still do these things, but now I think twice about them. I've heard of this thing called prudence, but it's such a shame to have to apply it to something so.......MONEY! CA$H MONEY!!! ARGHHHBLINGBLINGBLINGBLING<br /><br />But even more lastly, is self-improvement masturbation. I don't even agree with the statement that self-improvement is masturbation, (I think that's a fight club quote, which in itself is probably quoted from elsewhere.. so sue me i don't do my research) but if that's the general consensus then by all means call me a greater kitten-killen demon. I havent set foot in a gym in about 4 months, putting it off and keeping up w/ the upkeep in less direct, unintentional ways (ie falling off aircraft) But I need to start. I slobbed it all the way through summer but winter's my more favorite season anyway. (next to super-winter, then summer, and lastly super-summer, because that's how it is here...no nice seasons...just the shitty ones and extreme versions of them) I guess I should also start taking some actual college classes. I can fake the funk all I want but I still feel guilty whenever I put "some college" for my level of education on various registration questionnaires (does IB count? bahahhahaa) But I digress...<br /><br />see that's what you get. you complain that it's too quiet and you have turds like me post garbage. ELLIPSIS...FILLED...GARBAGE! The lazy man's device to keep a piece flowing...BOOYA<br /><br />
